messages.message: If you type a prompt and then change the advanced toggle it sends the prompt and sets the name automatically, but this can cause errors if you added a question mark to your prompt: https://www.loom.com/share/4be0b6b098da4cfeba1e5e33caec3295
cc: @Arjun @Prashant Kikani. @lydia looks like this was the issue you were brining up on the PR review :sweat_smile:

I think, the error shown in the video is fixed by @Kathy Wu in this PR:
https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/41114/files#diff-5e91ebedac6c951436fd297f78dbb961b1f4417117131be17352bb6d229396bcR41

Removing all the characters except `A-Za-z0-9_`

Also, in the `1.1.7` model-version, we're setting summary of the question(not the question itself) as the field-name. So, this should not happen once that model is deployed on the release branch.

Right now, it's `1.1.6` on the prod.
